WEBVTT

00:01.542 --> 00:02.623
PREVIOUSLY ON "REVENGE"...

00:02.623 --> 00:04.085
I'M IN POSSESSION
OF THE ONLY THING

00:04.085 --> 00:05.716
THAT COULD ONE DAY
EXONERATE YOU...

00:05.716 --> 00:07.128
A FULL CONFESSION
OF MY OWN.

00:07.128 --> 00:08.129
"VITO SPLENDIDO"
 MADE ME AN OFFER,

00:08.129 --> 00:10.261
AND I'M THINKING
ABOUT TAKING IT.

00:10.261 --> 00:11.632
JACK ENCOURAGED ME
TO GO.

00:11.632 --> 00:13.224
I THINK IT'S ODD THAT
HE'S TRYING TO PUSH YOU TO LEAVE

00:13.224 --> 00:15.056
NOW THAT EMILY'S SINGLE.

00:15.056 --> 00:16.306
YOU'RE TRYING TO
MANIPULATE ME.

00:16.306 --> 00:18.439
NO, I'M JUST TRYING TO
GET YOU TO OPEN YOUR EYES.

00:18.439 --> 00:22.022
DANIEL AND I FORCED MY FATHER
OUT OF "VOULEZ."

00:22.022 --> 00:23.274
IF THERE WAS ANY WAY
I COULD EXTRICATE YOU

00:23.274 --> 00:25.276
FROM THIS NEW BATTLE
WITH VICTORIA, I WOULD.

00:25.276 --> 00:27.068
IT'S TIME
I PUT SOMETHING TO BED.

00:27.068 --> 00:29.860
PASCAL,
I'VE GOT VICTORIA'S TRUMP CARD.

00:29.860 --> 00:31.282
Victoria:
I RECEIVED YOUR GIFT.

00:31.282 --> 00:33.033
I WILL NEVER BETRAY
YOU AGAIN.

00:34.915 --> 00:36.287
THE LETTER'S NOT ENOUGH
TO INCRIMINATE THE GRAYSONS,

00:36.287 --> 00:39.080
BUT PASCAL HAS A PIECE
OF THE PUZZLE THAT I DON'T.

00:39.080 --> 00:41.712
AIDEN.
 Aiden: "TWM" IS
TREVOR WARREN MATHIS.

00:41.712 --> 00:44.125
PASCAL WAS TALKING
ABOUT MY FATHER.

00:47.258 --> 00:51.632
Emily: AS CHILDREN, WE FLINCH
 AT THE SIGHT OF BLOOD,

00:51.632 --> 00:56.437
NOT YET REALIZING
 IT MEANS FAMILY, LOYALTY,

00:56.437 --> 00:59.230
AND IS THE ESSENCE OF LIFE.

00:59.230 --> 01:02.143
BUT FOR ALL ITS VIRTUE...
 FATHER?

01:02.143 --> 01:03.894
...THERE IS
 THE UNAVOIDABLE REALITY

01:03.894 --> 01:06.647
THAT BLOOD IS OFTEN
 THE CHILD OF PAIN...

01:08.239 --> 01:11.192
...AND A VIOLENT REMINDER
THAT ANYTHING CAN BE TAKEN AWAY

01:11.192 --> 01:14.115
IN THE BLINK OF AN EYE.

01:14.115 --> 01:15.116
NO!

01:15.116 --> 01:17.328
[ GASPS ]

01:17.328 --> 01:20.751
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

01:20.751 --> 01:22.333
Emily: HEY.

01:22.333 --> 01:24.755
YOU ALL RIGHT?

01:24.755 --> 01:26.127
YEAH.

01:26.127 --> 01:28.129
YEAH, I-I'M FINE.

01:28.129 --> 01:31.342
THINKING ABOUT THE PAST
DOESN'T MAKE FOR RESTFUL SLEEP.

01:31.342 --> 01:33.554
[ SIGHS ]

01:36.217 --> 01:38.018
YOU KNOW, I JUST WANT TO
MARCH NEXT DOOR

01:38.018 --> 01:39.600
AND ASK THAT BASTARD
WHAT HE DID TO MY FATHER,

01:39.600 --> 01:43.023
BUT I KNOW THAT WOULD
PUT PASCAL ON ALERT.

01:43.023 --> 01:44.395
WELL, ESPECIALLY SINCE
HE AND VICTORIA

01:44.395 --> 01:46.437
ARE ALREADY
CONSPIRING AGAINST ME.

01:47.988 --> 01:50.361
[ SIGHS ]
COME ON. I MADE SOME COFFEE.

01:50.361 --> 01:54.195
NOLAN HACKED INTO MY FATHER'S
PHONE AND EMPLOYMENT RECORDS,

01:54.195 --> 01:57.198
EVEN LOOKED INTO THE POLICE
INVESTIGATION AFTER HIS ARREST.

01:57.198 --> 01:59.200
NOTHING CAN LINK HIM
TO PASCAL OR ANYBODY

01:59.200 --> 02:01.242
IN THE DAYS LEADING UP
TO HIS MURDER, SO...

02:01.242 --> 02:04.295
THAT LETTER'S
STILL A MYSTERY.

02:04.295 --> 02:05.296
[ CELLPHONE THUDS ]

02:05.296 --> 02:07.087
WELL, THEN...

02:07.087 --> 02:09.669
MAYBE WE SHOULD
TALK ABOUT THAT TIME...

02:09.669 --> 02:11.252
SINCE WE HAVE
NOTHING ELSE TO GO ON.

02:11.252 --> 02:12.463
OH, WHAT'S THERE
TO TALK ABOUT?

02:12.463 --> 02:14.465
WE THOUGHT MY SISTER
HAD RUN AWAY.

02:14.465 --> 02:17.097
AND WHILE WE'RE REELING
FROM THAT, FLIGHT 197 HAPPENED.

02:17.097 --> 02:18.429
UH,
THE POLICE CAME 'ROUND,

02:18.429 --> 02:21.312
ASKING QUESTIONS ABOUT
WHO PUT THE BOMB ON THE PLANE.

02:21.312 --> 02:23.103
AND WHEN MY FATHER
SHOT HIMSELF,

02:23.103 --> 02:25.686
IT JUST CONFIRMED
WHAT EVERYBODY THOUGHT.

02:25.686 --> 02:28.359
THAT HE WAS A TERRORIST.

02:28.359 --> 02:33.153
WHICH I THOUGHT MYSELF
FOR MANY YEARS...

02:33.153 --> 02:37.368
UNTIL I FOUND OUT
COLLEEN HAD BEEN KIDNAPPED

02:37.368 --> 02:40.160
AND HE WAS FORCED
TO DO WHAT HE DID...

02:40.160 --> 02:43.204
WHICH JUST MADE HIS SUICIDE
EVEN MORE SHAMEFUL.

02:43.204 --> 02:46.997
HE TOOK THE COWARD'S WAY OUT.
SHE NEEDED A HERO.

02:46.997 --> 02:51.592
WELL, THERE IS
ONE MORE THING WE COULD TRY.

02:51.592 --> 02:53.464
BUT I CAN'T DO IT ALONE.

02:53.464 --> 02:56.257
WHATEVER YOU NEED.

02:59.179 --> 03:02.223
[ SEA GULLS CRYING ]

03:11.942 --> 03:14.865
[ WAVES CRASHING ]

03:18.529 --> 03:19.530
MORNING.

03:19.530 --> 03:22.122
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

03:25.326 --> 03:28.749
WAKING UP TO YOU
THESE PAST FEW MORNINGS...

03:28.749 --> 03:31.131
[ GASPS ]
I'VE MISSED FEELING LIKE THIS.

03:31.131 --> 03:33.964
YOU WERE WASTED ON CONRAD.
 [ LAUGHS ]

03:33.964 --> 03:35.676
IT WAS A MISTAKE.

03:35.676 --> 03:37.468
MARRYING
FOR ALL THE WRONG REASONS

03:37.468 --> 03:40.641
RESULTED IN SUCH MISERY,
HMM.

03:43.103 --> 03:44.605
LET ME DEAL WITH EMILY.

03:44.605 --> 03:46.807
NO. I WILL.

03:46.807 --> 03:48.148
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

03:48.148 --> 03:50.311
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

03:50.311 --> 03:52.483
MM.
 MNH-MNH.

03:52.483 --> 03:55.656
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

03:55.656 --> 03:57.448
I'LL COME BACK.

04:00.120 --> 04:02.032
YES?

04:02.032 --> 04:05.075
MR. GRAYSON IS HERE FOR YOU,
MR. LeMARCHAL.

04:08.749 --> 04:11.632
[ DOOR OPENS ]

04:11.632 --> 04:13.173
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

04:13.173 --> 04:15.796
LOOK, I GET WHY YOU'RE MAD,
OKAY,

04:15.796 --> 04:18.218
BUT THIS SILENT TREATMENT'S
LASTED THREE DAYS.

04:18.218 --> 04:20.089
AND NOW THAT
I'M BACK AT "VOULEZ,"

04:20.089 --> 04:21.341
I WANT YOU THERE, TOO.

04:21.341 --> 04:23.344
YOU USED ME
TO TURN MARGAUX AGAINST JACK.

04:23.344 --> 04:24.555
I JUST TRIED TO
GET YOU BOTH

04:24.555 --> 04:27.057
TO SEE THE LIGHT
ABOUT THAT GUY.

04:27.057 --> 04:31.191
I'M SORRY FOR THE WAY I DID IT,
ALL RIGHT?

04:31.191 --> 04:33.193
JUST SO YOU KNOW,
YOUR LITTLE PLAN DIDN'T WORK.

04:33.193 --> 04:35.356
I'M HELPING JACK
WITH HIS MOVE.

04:35.356 --> 04:39.199
CHAR, I'M NOT
MAKING THIS UP, OKAY?

04:39.199 --> 04:41.161
YOU KNOW
HOW TIGHT HE IS WITH EMILY.

04:41.161 --> 04:43.324
TELL ME YOU'VE NEVER WONDERED
WHAT THEIR CONNECTION IS.

04:43.324 --> 04:45.326
I DON'T CARE.

04:45.326 --> 04:47.328
CARL'S MY NEPHEW.

04:47.328 --> 04:49.119
AND JACK HAS NEVER BEEN
ANYTHING BUT NICE TO ME.

04:49.119 --> 04:52.122
AND WHAT IF YOU'RE
BLINDLY DEFENDING THE MAN

04:52.122 --> 04:54.755
WHO'S HELPING EMILY
DEMOLISH THIS FAMILY?

04:54.755 --> 04:57.678
COULD YOU EVER
FORGIVE YOURSELF?

05:04.264 --> 05:10.270
AH, I SENSE THE STENCH
OF ROMANCE IS IN THE AIR.

05:10.270 --> 05:13.103
I WON'T TALK ABOUT HER.

05:13.103 --> 05:15.696
[ CHUCKLES ] THAT'S NOT VICTORIA
I WAS REFERENCING.

05:15.696 --> 05:19.440
WELL, IT SEEMS THAT THE ONLY
KINDNESS YOU'LL GRANT ME

05:19.440 --> 05:21.862
AFTER I GAVE YOU LEVERAGE
TO GET INTO HER BED

05:21.862 --> 05:24.705
IS TO KEEP HER
OUT OF THIS CONVERSATION.

05:24.705 --> 05:25.946
I OWE YOU NOTHING,
OKAY?

05:25.946 --> 05:27.207
YOU CAN LOOK ME
IN THE EYE

05:27.207 --> 05:28.579
AND TELL ME THAT
YOU'RE RENEGING ON OUR DEAL

05:28.579 --> 05:30.000
INSTEAD OF HIDING OUT
AND PLAYING HOUSE.

05:30.000 --> 05:32.212
AND WHILE YOU NURSE THE WOUNDS
OF YOUR NEW LOSS,

05:32.212 --> 05:35.005
I'M ALREADY BREAKING
IN TO THE SOUTH AMERICAN MARKET.

05:35.005 --> 05:37.758
[ CHUCKLES ] YOU WOULDN'T KNOW
WHERE TO BEGIN.

05:37.758 --> 05:42.172
ALBERTO LOYA JUMPED
AT THE MENTION OF MY NAME...

05:42.172 --> 05:45.466
MUCH LIKE PEOPLE ONCE DID
AT THE MENTION OF YOURS.

05:45.466 --> 05:46.967
OUR BUSINESS IS DONE.

05:56.276 --> 05:59.069
[ BRAKES SQUEAK ]

06:07.077 --> 06:10.701
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

06:13.253 --> 06:17.047
[ SIGHS ]
HELLO, MOTHER.

06:17.047 --> 06:20.501
AIDEN.

06:22.172 --> 06:35.476
THIS IS EMILY...
MY FIANCéE.

06:39.570 --> 06:40.821
Harriet: IT WAS MY
LATE HUSBAND'S GRANDMOTHER'S.

06:40.821 --> 06:42.943
I'VE LOVED IT EVER SINCE
HE PUT IT ON MY FINGER.

06:42.943 --> 06:45.946
AND HAVE YOU SET A DATE?

06:45.946 --> 06:47.738
NO. NO, NOT YET.

06:47.738 --> 06:50.531
OH, IT'S SO DARK IN HERE.
YOU NEVER OPEN THE CURTAINS.

06:50.531 --> 06:52.453
NO. PEOPLE STILL TALK.

06:52.453 --> 06:55.335
OH, WELL, I --
I DOUBT THAT.

06:55.335 --> 06:56.797
IS THAT WHY I HAVEN'T
SEEN YOU IN EIGHT YEARS?

06:56.797 --> 07:00.380
WELL, EMILY,
UH, MADE ME REALIZE

07:00.380 --> 07:04.384
I'VE NOT BEEN DEALING WITH
EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED, SO...

07:04.384 --> 07:06.597
THAT'S -- THAT'S WHY
WE'RE HERE, YEAH?

07:06.597 --> 07:08.388
THEN MAYBE
YOU CAN HELP HIM UNDERSTAND

07:08.388 --> 07:10.260
WHY THIS SUBJECT
IS BEST LEFT ALONE, EMILY.

07:10.260 --> 07:13.934
MUM, WELL...
MAYBE IT WOULD BE GOOD TO TALK,

07:13.934 --> 07:16.356
YOU KNOW, HELP --
HELP DEAL WITH THINGS AND --

07:16.356 --> 07:18.058
AND -- AND YOU, TOO,
YOU KNOW?

07:18.058 --> 07:20.821
UM...I MEAN, YOU'VE --

07:20.821 --> 07:22.613
YOU'VE BEEN
HOLING YOURSELF UP IN HERE --

07:22.613 --> 07:24.324
THIS IS MY LIFE.

07:24.324 --> 07:26.697
YOU WANTED OUT.
YOU GOT OUT.

07:28.328 --> 07:31.371
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

07:31.371 --> 07:34.745
I KNEW WE SHOULDN'T
HAVE COME HERE.

07:34.745 --> 07:37.337
I DON'T WANT TO CAUSE HER
ANY MORE PAIN, EMILY.

07:37.337 --> 07:39.129
YEAH, BUT IF WE CAN FIND
WHAT THE CONNECTION WAS

07:39.129 --> 07:40.921
BETWEEN PASCAL
AND YOUR FATHER,

07:40.921 --> 07:43.844
THEN MAYBE WE COULD
TAKE SOME OF THAT PAIN AWAY.

07:49.349 --> 07:51.972
OH!
 [ LAUGHTER ]

07:51.972 --> 07:53.554
Jack: HEY.

07:53.554 --> 07:56.186
GUESS WHO'S THE PROUD OWNER
OF A 30-YEAR MORTGAGE.

07:56.186 --> 07:58.438
OOH.
 WE CAN MOVE IN
WHENEVER WE WANT.

07:58.438 --> 08:00.400
CONGRATULATIONS, JACK.

08:00.400 --> 08:02.272
I'M SORRY
I WASN'T THERE.

08:02.272 --> 08:04.404
NO WORRIES.

08:04.404 --> 08:05.405
[ CARL COOS ]
 HEY, KID.

08:05.405 --> 08:07.407
YOU JUST
GOT YOURSELF A YARD.

08:07.407 --> 08:09.279
WE SHOULD CELEBRATE.
 [ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

08:09.279 --> 08:10.531
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:10.531 --> 08:12.783
♪ RECALL THE DAYS I WAITED
 FOR YOU ♪

08:12.783 --> 08:14.414
[ BEEP ]

08:14.414 --> 08:17.207
Margaux: HELLO?

08:17.207 --> 08:18.498
NO, I DIDN'T KNOW.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.420
I'M ON MY WAY, YES.
 [ CARL LAUGHING ]

08:20.420 --> 08:22.042
[ BEEP ]

08:22.042 --> 08:23.584
I'M SORRY.
 IT'S OKAY, BABE.

08:23.584 --> 08:24.715
GO AHEAD.

08:24.715 --> 08:26.717
DON'T FORGET YOUR KEYS.

08:26.717 --> 08:29.469
Stevie: THAT'S RIGHT.
LET'S GET YOU OUT OF THE SUN.

08:29.469 --> 08:30.891
THERE YOU GO.
THERE YOU GO.

08:30.891 --> 08:32.432
♪ YOU ARE MORE
 THAN JUST A DREAM ♪

08:32.432 --> 08:34.845
♪ YOU WERE OUT OF MY LEAGUE ♪

08:34.845 --> 08:36.727
WHAT'S WRONG, JACK?

08:36.727 --> 08:40.350
MARGAUX'S FIRST MOVE
WAS RE-HIRING DANIEL GRAYSON.

08:40.350 --> 08:42.352
HIS FIRST MOVE
WAS TRYING TO SPLIT US UP

08:42.352 --> 08:43.693
BY TELLING HER
THAT I HAD FEELINGS FOR EMILY.

08:43.693 --> 08:46.697
IF A WOMAN
FALLS FOR THAT...

08:46.697 --> 08:49.239
SHE MUST THINK
THERE'S SOMETHING TO IT.

08:49.239 --> 08:51.451
♪ OOH-OOH-OOH,
 OOH-OOH-OOH-OOH-OOH-OOH ♪

08:51.451 --> 08:52.532
[ Chuckling ] RUDY.

08:52.532 --> 08:54.745
RUDY, MY COMPETITORS
READ YOUR FEED,

08:54.745 --> 08:59.419
SO, NO SPOILER ALERTS,
BUT TRUST ME --

08:59.419 --> 09:03.834
THIS LAUNCH
IS GONNA BE BEYOND REDIC.

09:03.834 --> 09:06.216
THE PROGRAM IS CALLED MYCLONE,

09:06.216 --> 09:09.630
AND IT'LL HAVE YOU
TALKING TO YOURSELF IN NO TIME.

09:09.630 --> 09:10.931
[ CHUCKLES ]

09:10.931 --> 09:13.724
[ BEEP ]
 ARE YOU ROMANCING
THE BLOGOSPHERE?

09:13.724 --> 09:16.176
SEE, TECHIES LOVE IT
WHEN YOU CALL.

09:16.176 --> 09:20.100
IT MAKES THEM FEEL SO...
RETRO.

09:20.100 --> 09:22.482
AND SPEAKING OF,

09:22.482 --> 09:26.396
MY LAWYER SENT OVER
OUR BUSINESS CONTRACT --

09:26.396 --> 09:29.359
OLD-SCHOOL HARD COPIES.

09:29.359 --> 09:31.401
I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE

09:31.401 --> 09:33.193
WE ARE GOING INTO
BUSINESS TOGETHER.

09:33.193 --> 09:35.956
[ CHUCKLES ]
WELL, BELIEVE IT, PARTNER.

09:35.956 --> 09:38.368
[ BEEP ]
 PARTNER?

09:38.368 --> 09:39.750
YO,
WHY DOES THIS SAY THAT

09:39.750 --> 09:41.912
YOU PLAN TO OWN
70% OF THE COMPANY?

09:41.912 --> 09:45.255
THE PROGRAM
WON'T BE MARKET-READY

09:45.255 --> 09:48.258
UNTIL I IRON IT OUT,
AND, UH,

09:48.258 --> 09:51.672
I'M ASSUMING ALL THE
FINANCIAL RISK HERE, SO...

09:51.672 --> 09:53.303
YOU HAVE PLENTY OF BANK.
INVESTING IN THIS --

09:53.303 --> 09:55.385
IT DOESN'T
PUT YOU IN THE POORHOUSE,

09:55.385 --> 09:56.847
BUT IT DOES PUT
YOU BACK ON TOP, RIGHT?

09:56.847 --> 09:59.139
EXCUSE ME?
 YOUR LAST IDEA --

09:59.139 --> 10:01.892
IF MEMORY SERVES,
IT LANDED YOU ON MY CELLBLOCK.

10:01.892 --> 10:05.105
AND BEFORE THAT,
WAS I EVEN BORN YET?

10:06.687 --> 10:08.278
WOW.

10:08.278 --> 10:10.901
THAT'S A LOW BLOW,
I MEAN, EVEN FOR YOU.

10:10.901 --> 10:13.073
[ CHUCKLES ]
 LOOK, ANY OTHER INVESTOR

10:13.073 --> 10:16.616
WOULD ASK FOR MUCH MORE
AND CARE A LOT LESS.

10:16.616 --> 10:20.240
WELL, MAYBE I SHOULD
FIND OUT FOR MYSELF.

10:24.294 --> 10:26.296
♪ SHOW ME UP ♪

10:26.296 --> 10:28.128
Pascal: I GOT YOUR MESSAGE.
 [ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

10:28.128 --> 10:30.340
WHAT'S SO URGENT
IT COULDN'T WAIT?

10:30.340 --> 10:31.341
♪ SHOW ME UP ♪

10:31.341 --> 10:32.342
I'LL BE BACK.

10:32.342 --> 10:33.924
♪ SHOW ME UP ♪

10:33.924 --> 10:35.345
♪ SHOW ME UP ♪

10:35.345 --> 10:39.139
WHY IS MY BROTHER
IN MIAMI TO NEGOTIATE A DEAL

10:39.139 --> 10:41.932
AS IMPORTANT AS INCREASING
OUR STAKE IN THE AMERICAS?

10:41.932 --> 10:44.144
I WAS RIGHT HERE.

10:44.144 --> 10:47.527
WELL, I'VE DECIDED TO
STEP DOWN IN TWO YEARS.

10:47.527 --> 10:50.480
I THINK IT'S TIME
FOR ME TO ENJOY OTHER THINGS.

10:50.480 --> 10:52.983
I SENT GIDEON
'CAUSE HE IS TO TAKE OVER.

10:54.404 --> 10:57.037
YOU'RE GROOMING HIM
 TO RUN THINGS?

10:57.037 --> 10:59.740
HE HAS SHOWN LOYALTY
AND DETERMINATION.

10:59.740 --> 11:01.201
YOU PULLED AWAY
AT EVERY TURN.

11:01.201 --> 11:04.995
I GOT INTO THE BEST SCHOOLS
ON MERIT,

11:04.995 --> 11:08.418
WORKED FROM THE BOTTOM UP
AT OUR COMPETITORS,

11:08.418 --> 11:12.793
AND APPROACHED YOU
ONLY WHEN I WAS READY.

11:12.793 --> 11:15.796
THAT'S WHY I ASKED TO LAUNCH
 "VOULEZ" IN THE STATES.

11:15.796 --> 11:17.798
THIS HAS NEVER BEEN
MY FINAL STOP.

11:17.798 --> 11:19.800
THEN WHY MAKE PLANS
TO BECOME

11:19.800 --> 11:22.642
A PART-TIME WIFE
AND STEPMOTHER, HUH?

11:22.642 --> 11:24.224
OF COURSE
YOU CAN'T COMPREHEND A WOMAN

11:24.224 --> 11:26.356
WHO CAN WORK
 AND HAVE A LIFE.

11:26.356 --> 11:28.608
[ SCOFFS ]
 THAT'S WHY
YOU CAME BACK FOR VICTORIA.

11:28.608 --> 11:31.111
I IMAGINE SHE'S SITTING
AT HOME WAITING FOR YOU.

11:32.022 --> 11:33.693
I HAVE WORK TO DO.

11:36.316 --> 11:38.989
[ BUZZER ]

11:38.989 --> 11:43.413
[ INDISTINCT TALKING OVER P.A. ]

11:45.285 --> 11:47.707
IT'S BEEN FAR TOO LONG.

11:47.707 --> 11:52.332
WHAT A SURPRISE,
ALBEIT AN HONOR,

11:52.332 --> 11:56.216
TO RECEIVE A VISIT
FROM THE QUEEN HERSELF.

12:02.102 --> 12:03.183
YOU LOOK WELL, MASON.

12:03.183 --> 12:05.305
AND YOU STILL LIE ELEGANTLY,
VICTORIA.

12:05.305 --> 12:07.938
MY SKIN IS SALLOW
AND MY WIT SQUANDERED,

12:07.938 --> 12:10.060
THOUGH I TAKE SOLACE
KNOWING THAT

12:10.060 --> 12:12.903
I WALK IN THE SHACKLED FOOTSTEPS
OF THE GREATS --

12:12.903 --> 12:15.695
CERVANTES, WILDE,
VOLTAIRE,

12:15.695 --> 12:17.948
ALL IMPRISONED AS I.

12:17.948 --> 12:21.912
NOW, TO WHAT
DO I OWE THIS PLEASURE?

12:21.912 --> 12:23.824
EMILY THORNE --

12:23.824 --> 12:27.077
SHE'S BEEN SNIFFING AROUND
MY FAMILY'S HISTORY.

12:27.077 --> 12:29.289
AND AS I TAKE A STEP BACK,
I CAN'T HELP BUT NOTICE

12:29.289 --> 12:31.751
HER TIES
TO ONE THING IN PARTICULAR.

12:31.751 --> 12:33.543
I CAN'T IMAGINE WHAT.

12:33.543 --> 12:36.967
NOW, YOU'RE THE PREMIER EXPERT
ON THE SUBJECT.

12:36.967 --> 12:39.219
DID EMILY'S NAME
EVER COME UP IN YOUR RESEARCH?

12:39.219 --> 12:40.640
[ BUZZER ]

12:40.640 --> 12:43.053
I WILL SAY THIS.

12:43.053 --> 12:45.555
I WAS VERY INTERESTED IN EMILY
AT ONE POINT.

12:45.555 --> 12:47.647
WHAT WAS THE GENESIS
OF YOUR SUSPICION?

12:47.647 --> 12:49.149
[ CHUCKLES ]

12:49.149 --> 12:52.102
IF YOU THINK I'M GOING TO
SPILL MY SECRETS FOR NOTHING,

12:52.102 --> 12:54.154
YOUR HUBRIS
IS AS OFFENSIVE

12:54.154 --> 12:56.566
AS MY FORMER CELLMATE'S
GROOMING HABITS.

12:56.566 --> 12:58.778
OH, WELL,
WHAT WOULD OUR VISIT BE

12:58.778 --> 13:01.111
WITHOUT
A HINT OF THE MERCENARY?

13:01.111 --> 13:03.323
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

13:03.323 --> 13:04.404
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

13:04.404 --> 13:07.167
A BRUNCH OF LOBSTER BENEDICT
AND A GIBSON

13:07.167 --> 13:09.119
AT BELLA MONICA'S...

13:09.119 --> 13:12.752
AS FREE MAN BY, SAY...

13:12.752 --> 13:14.915
END OF THE MONTH?

13:14.915 --> 13:16.086
[ BUZZER ]

13:16.086 --> 13:18.718
OH, I'D LOVE A TABLE
BY THE WINDOW...

13:18.718 --> 13:20.720
IF YOU CAN SWING IT.

13:20.720 --> 13:22.092
GUARD!

13:22.092 --> 13:23.723
Guard:
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO, TREADWELL.

13:27.517 --> 13:30.100
[ GLASS CLINKS ]

13:32.732 --> 13:35.775
OH, DID I WAKE YOU?

13:35.775 --> 13:38.398
NO, NO, I WAS JUST GONNA
GRAB A GLASS OF WATER.

13:38.398 --> 13:42.702
I DON'T SLEEP MOST NIGHTS,
SO I CLEAN.

13:42.702 --> 13:44.284
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

13:44.284 --> 13:46.156
I'M SORRY ABOUT TODAY.

13:46.156 --> 13:49.950
AIDEN'S JUST
LOOKING FOR CLOSURE.

13:49.950 --> 13:53.623
YOU'RE MARRYING A MAN
WITH THE BROKEN HEART

13:53.623 --> 13:55.835
OF A 12-YEAR-OLD BOY.

13:55.835 --> 13:57.797
AND I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO HELP YOU HEAL IT.

13:57.797 --> 14:03.263
WELL, THAT'S...
SORT OF WHAT BONDED US.

14:03.263 --> 14:06.266
MY FATHER DIED
WHEN I WAS YOUNG, TOO.

14:06.266 --> 14:09.429
I'M SORRY TO HEAR THAT,
EMILY...

14:09.429 --> 14:13.233
THOUGH TRY TO IMAGINE SUCH
A LOSS MADE WORSE BY SCANDAL.

14:13.233 --> 14:17.107
TREVOR AND AIDEN
WERE SO CLOSE.

14:17.107 --> 14:20.360
SPENT HOURS IN THE SHED
DOING ALL SORTS OF PROJECTS.

14:20.360 --> 14:22.822
AFTER THAT PLANE CRASH,

14:22.822 --> 14:25.485
TREVOR SHUT HIM OUT
AND HID BACK THERE ALONE.

14:25.485 --> 14:28.909
HE MUST HAVE FELT
SO ABANDONED.

14:28.909 --> 14:31.081
STILL, AT LEAST
HE DEFENDED HIS FATHER,

14:31.081 --> 14:34.084
EVEN THOUGH HIS CLASSMATES
CALLED HIM A MURDERER.

14:34.084 --> 14:36.046
AND WHAT DID HE GET
IN RETURN?

14:36.046 --> 14:39.709
THE HONOR
OF FINDING TREVOR DEAD.

14:39.709 --> 14:43.093
AIDEN FOUND HIM?

14:45.425 --> 14:47.637
[ SIGHS ]
I NEVER KNEW.

14:47.637 --> 14:49.509
EVERYTHING CHANGED
SO QUICKLY --

14:49.509 --> 14:53.603
HIS SISTER RUNNING AWAY,
HIS FATHER TAKING HIS LIFE,

14:53.603 --> 14:55.185
AND ME TRYING TO
WRAP MY HEAD AROUND

14:55.185 --> 14:59.779
THAT VERSION OF A STRANGER
I MARRIED.

14:59.779 --> 15:02.983
I'M GLAD HE'S FOUND A LITTLE
PIECE OF HAPPINESS WITH YOU.

15:02.983 --> 15:05.735
I CAN ONLY HOPE THE SAME
FOR COLLEEN.

15:05.735 --> 15:07.787
YOUR DAUGHTER?

15:07.787 --> 15:10.790
I KNOW
IT'S BEEN YEARS...

15:10.790 --> 15:14.294
BUT I HOPE THE LIFE
SHE RAN AWAY TO IS A HAPPY ONE.

15:27.097 --> 15:30.260
I AM FLATTERED,
MR. GRAYSON, BUT...

15:30.260 --> 15:32.682
MY NEGOTIATIONS WITH PASCAL
AND LeMARCHAL MEDIA

15:32.682 --> 15:34.054
ARE TOO FAR ALONG.

15:34.054 --> 15:36.266
WE ARE IN FINAL TALKS.
 [ SCOFFS ]

15:36.266 --> 15:38.478
YOUR SOUTH AMERICAN
MEDIA CONGLOMERATE

15:38.478 --> 15:41.441
IS THE BELLE OF THE BALL,
AND YET YOUR FRIEND PASCAL

15:41.441 --> 15:43.063
DIDN'T DEEM YOU WORTHY
TO MEET IN PERSON.

15:43.063 --> 15:45.025
HE HAD PRESSING BUSINESS
IN NEW YORK.

15:45.025 --> 15:46.276
HE'S A BUSY MAN.

15:46.276 --> 15:48.568
WELL, THAT BUSINESS
IS SCREWING MY EX-WIFE.

15:48.568 --> 15:49.909
AND HE'S ALSO
SCREWING YOU

15:49.909 --> 15:51.331
BY NOT GIVING YOU
FULL DISCLOSURE.

15:51.331 --> 15:53.203
WITHIN TWO YEARS,
YOU'LL BE DOING BUSINESS

15:53.203 --> 15:55.245
WITH HIS KID,
NOT PASCAL.

15:55.245 --> 15:58.168
WHERE DID YOU HEAR THIS?

15:58.168 --> 16:00.210
I OVERHEARD GIDEON
THROWING HIS NEW TITLE AROUND

16:00.210 --> 16:01.541
WITH THE CONCIERGE.

16:01.541 --> 16:03.293
SPECIOUS BRAVADO
HAS BEEN THE KID'S CALLING CARD

16:03.293 --> 16:04.634
SINCE HE WAS 15...

16:04.634 --> 16:07.677
WHEREAS...

16:07.677 --> 16:09.679
THIS IS MINE.

16:09.679 --> 16:11.591
CALL ME OPTIMISTIC,
BUT...

16:11.591 --> 16:15.185
WELCOME TO GRAYSON MEDIA.

16:15.185 --> 16:17.227
[ TELEPHONES RINGING ]

16:21.481 --> 16:24.694
OH, I CAN FEEL THE ANGER
FROM HERE.

16:24.694 --> 16:27.907
MY FATHER
IS STEPPING DOWN

16:27.907 --> 16:31.281
AND HANDING OVER THE COMPANY
TO MY IDIOT BROTHER.

16:31.281 --> 16:33.953
WHICH ONE?
NOT -- NOT GIDEON?

16:35.075 --> 16:37.037
HUH. I'M SURE
HE HAS HIS REASONS.

16:37.037 --> 16:38.668
WELL, THEY'RE OBVIOUS.

16:38.668 --> 16:40.330
HE'S A MAN. I'M NOT.

16:40.330 --> 16:42.212
AND WHILE
GIDEON'S ONLY LEARNED

16:42.212 --> 16:43.623
HOW TO USE
THE CORPORATE CARD,

16:43.623 --> 16:46.886
I'VE STUDIED EVERY SINGLE DEAL
PASCAL HAS EVER MADE.

16:46.886 --> 16:48.128
I'VE BUILT
A SUCCESSFUL BUSINESS,

16:48.128 --> 16:50.840
BUT YET THE ONLY THING
THAT MAN SEES

16:50.840 --> 16:53.183
IS ME THROWING MY LIFE AWAY
FOR JACK.

16:53.183 --> 16:55.265
AY!
 OOH. HEY, HEY.

16:55.265 --> 16:58.438
DON'T LET HIM GET TO YOU.
OKAY? HE'S NOT WORTH IT.

16:58.438 --> 17:00.850
[ SIGHS ]

17:00.850 --> 17:02.642
NO, YOU'RE RIGHT.

17:02.642 --> 17:04.983
YOU'RE RIGHT.
[ SIGHS ]

17:07.527 --> 17:09.148
THIS IS GONNA BRUISE.

17:09.148 --> 17:10.740
[ CHUCKLES ]

17:10.740 --> 17:13.823
I'M SORRY. I DIDN'T MEAN FOR YOU
TO SEE THIS SIDE OF ME.

17:13.823 --> 17:16.205
I KIND OF LIKE IT.

17:16.205 --> 17:17.287
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

17:17.287 --> 17:18.708
I'LL GET YOU SOME ICE,
OKAY?

17:18.708 --> 17:20.079
YEAH. THANK YOU.

17:22.872 --> 17:24.042
JACK.

17:24.042 --> 17:27.257
WHAT A NICE SURPRISE.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.670
YOU OKAY?

17:30.670 --> 17:32.092
[ SIGHS ]

17:32.092 --> 17:35.175
YEAH, MY FATHER --
HE MAKES ME SO ANGRY.

17:35.175 --> 17:36.346
WHAT DID HE DO?

17:36.346 --> 17:40.100
NO, FORGET ABOUT IT.

17:40.100 --> 17:41.351
WHY? 'CAUSE DANIEL
TALKED YOU DOWN?

17:41.351 --> 17:44.444
YEAH. I SAW THAT.

17:47.687 --> 17:49.689
DANIEL AND I
ARE FRIENDS.

17:49.689 --> 17:53.113
[ SCOFFS ]
 I DON'T LIKE JEALOUS MEN.

17:54.784 --> 17:56.786
I'LL SEE YOU LATER.

18:08.007 --> 18:10.009
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

18:13.173 --> 18:14.594
[ BEEP ]

18:14.594 --> 18:16.015
HELLO?

18:16.015 --> 18:17.597
[ BUZZER ]

18:17.597 --> 18:19.479
BAD TIME?

18:21.141 --> 18:23.313
NO CONTACT --
THAT WAS OUR AGREEMENT.

18:23.313 --> 18:24.984
When exactly

18:24.984 --> 18:26.726
DO YOU INTEND TO KEEP UP
YOUR END OF THE DEAL?

18:26.726 --> 18:28.938
WHEN I'M FINISHED.

18:28.938 --> 18:31.151
You were almost killed
after a marriage

18:31.151 --> 18:32.492
I CAN ONLY IMAGINE
WAS SUPPOSED TO

18:32.492 --> 18:33.943
HAVE A VERY DIFFERENT
HONEYMOON.

18:33.943 --> 18:35.074
[ BUZZER ]

18:35.074 --> 18:36.616
I COULD HAVE BEEN
STUCK IN HERE FOREVER,

18:36.616 --> 18:39.239
SPOTTING A GUY NAMED LITTLE SHIV
ON THE BENCH PRESS.

18:39.239 --> 18:40.330
I WANT TO RENEGOTIATE.

18:40.330 --> 18:41.701
YOU HAVE NO LEVERAGE.

18:41.701 --> 18:44.294
AH [CHUCKLES]
BUT I DO.

18:44.294 --> 18:45.745
I HAD A VISITOR.

18:45.745 --> 18:47.297
We gabbed
about old times,

18:47.297 --> 18:50.129
LAUGHED ABOUT
A CERTAIN JUVIE GIRL.

18:50.129 --> 18:53.843
[ INHALES DEEPLY,
SIGHS ]

18:53.843 --> 18:56.426
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

18:56.426 --> 18:59.098
To know how you intend to
keep your promise to me.

18:59.098 --> 19:00.470
SHOW ME YOUR HAND
WITHIN 24 HOURS,

19:00.470 --> 19:03.102
OR I'LL SHOW
MY VISITOR MINE.

19:03.102 --> 19:05.185
TICKTOCK
GOES THE CLARKE.

19:05.185 --> 19:07.857
[ SIGHS ]

19:15.405 --> 19:16.486
MASON KNOWS WHO YOU ARE?

19:16.486 --> 19:18.618
YES, AND HE THREATENED
TO EXPOSE ME,

19:18.618 --> 19:19.829
SO I SHUT HIM DOWN.

19:19.829 --> 19:21.581
NOLAN: Oh,
and she's being delicate.

19:21.581 --> 19:24.414
YOU FRAMED MASON
FOR CRIMES HE DIDN'T COMMIT

19:24.414 --> 19:26.996
AND THEN FORCED HIM
TO CONFESS TO THEM.

19:26.996 --> 19:29.209
WHY WOULD HE AGREE
TO THAT?

19:29.209 --> 19:31.591
'CAUSE HE'S A CELEB AUTHOR
WITH ONLY ONE BEST SELLER.

19:31.591 --> 19:34.003
SHE PROMISED HIM
THE EXCLUSIVE RIGHTS

19:34.003 --> 19:35.755
TO HER STORY OF REVENGE.

19:35.755 --> 19:37.757
NOW VICTORIA
IS TEMPTING HIM.

19:37.757 --> 19:39.008
I'M WORRIED HE'LL TALK.

19:39.008 --> 19:42.972
SO, EMS, WHAT DO WE DO?
YOU'RE IN JOLLY OLE.

19:42.972 --> 19:44.604
We can't exactly
traipse in there.

19:44.604 --> 19:46.226
THEY RECORD
EVERY CONVERSATION.

19:46.226 --> 19:48.938
NO. NO, THEY DON'T.

19:49.569 --> 19:51.020
JACK.
 No.

19:51.020 --> 19:52.772
I'M NOT GONNA LET THIS HACK
RAILROAD YOU, EMILY, OKAY?

19:52.772 --> 19:54.364
[ CLEARING THROAT ]

19:54.364 --> 19:56.776
[ BEEP ]

19:56.776 --> 19:58.948
HEY, I HEARD THERE WAS
A NEW HOMEOWNER IN TOWN.

19:58.948 --> 20:02.161
CHARLIE, TAKING A BREAK
FROM DISTRACTING MY JUVENILE,

20:02.161 --> 20:04.454
WHO, ONCE AGAIN,
HAS GONE DELINQUENT.

20:04.454 --> 20:08.668
YES, NOLAN,
I THOUGHT I'D SEE MY NEPHEW

20:08.668 --> 20:10.209
AND MAYBE THE NEW HOUSE.

20:10.209 --> 20:11.631
[ CHUCKLES ]
CARL'S OUT WITH STEVIE,

20:11.631 --> 20:13.633
AND I CAN'T --
I CAN'T LEAVE RIGHT NOW.

20:13.633 --> 20:15.044
WELL, IF YOU'RE
STARTING TO PACK,

20:15.044 --> 20:16.636
I'VE GOT SOME BOXES
IN THE CAR.

20:16.636 --> 20:19.469
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
I'M, UH -- I'M SORRY, CHARLOTTE,

20:19.469 --> 20:21.391
BUT, UM, WE'RE KIND OF
BUSY RIGHT NOW.

20:21.391 --> 20:23.182
WAS THAT EMILY?

20:23.182 --> 20:24.644
AND WHO'S
TRYING TO RAILROAD HER?

20:24.644 --> 20:26.726
I'LL, UH --
I'LL HAVE TO CALL YOU LATER.

20:26.726 --> 20:28.938
THANKS FOR THE BOXES.

20:28.938 --> 20:30.770
YEAH, SURE.

20:40.450 --> 20:43.663
WHAT HAPPENED?
MY MOM STAND YOU UP?

20:43.663 --> 20:45.415
SHE'S LATE.

20:45.415 --> 20:47.627
THE GREAT
PASCAL LeMARCHAL

20:47.627 --> 20:49.789
WRAPPED AROUND
A WOMAN'S FINGER.

20:49.789 --> 20:51.791
[ CHUCKLES ]
 I COULD SAY THE SAME.

20:51.791 --> 20:53.633
MY DAUGHTER FIRES YOU,

20:53.633 --> 20:55.715
AND YOU RUN BACK
AT THE FIRST OPPORTUNITY.

20:55.715 --> 20:57.717
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU'RE TOTALLY OBLIVIOUS

20:57.717 --> 21:00.089
TO WHAT AN AMAZING DAUGHTER
YOU HAVE, AREN'T YOU?

21:00.089 --> 21:01.431
I GIVE HER CREDIT
WHERE IT'S DUE.

21:01.431 --> 21:02.682
NO, YOU DON'T.

21:02.682 --> 21:04.684
NO, Y-YOU'VE GOT HER
PIGEONHOLED AT THIS MAGAZINE

21:04.684 --> 21:06.766
WHEN SHE'S CAPABLE
OF SO MUCH MORE.

21:06.766 --> 21:09.479
YOU WERE ALWAYS
SO FOND OF HER.

21:10.850 --> 21:13.022
YEAH, I STILL AM...

21:13.022 --> 21:14.814
AS MY BUSINESS PARTNER.

21:14.814 --> 21:16.526
SHE'S GOT A BOYFRIEND,
REMEMBER?

21:16.526 --> 21:18.818
IT'S HARD TO RECALL SINCE
SHE NEVER BRINGS HIM AROUND.

21:18.818 --> 21:21.611
I MET HIM BRIEFLY
AT THE OPERA.

21:21.611 --> 21:24.243
YEAH, AND I'M SURE
HE SEEMED LIKE A --

21:24.243 --> 21:26.075
A REAL NICE GUY.

21:26.075 --> 21:27.537
ISN'T HE?

21:27.537 --> 21:29.709
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

21:29.709 --> 21:32.752
WHAT I DO KNOW IS THAT

21:32.752 --> 21:35.254
SHE'S ALWAYS WANTED
YOUR LOVE AND RESPECT.

21:35.254 --> 21:37.467
AND I JUST HOPE
THAT SHE'S NOT

21:37.467 --> 21:39.629
SETTLING FOR SOMETHING
LESS THAN SHE DESERVES

21:39.629 --> 21:42.722
BECAUSE YOU NEVER TOLD HER
THAT SHE WAS WORTHY.

21:42.722 --> 21:46.185
ALL RIGHT.
SEE YOU AROUND.

21:49.559 --> 21:51.731
WHEN I HEARD
I HAD NEW COUNSEL,

21:51.731 --> 21:55.695
I'D NEVER IMAGINED I'D RATE
THE ONE AND ONLY STEVIE GRAYSON.

21:55.695 --> 21:57.857
HAVE WE MET BEFORE?
 NO.

21:57.857 --> 22:00.490
BUT I CERTAINLY
DINED ON YOUR REPUTATION

22:00.490 --> 22:01.651
WHEN I WAS
A YOUNG JOURNALIST

22:01.651 --> 22:03.282
COVERING NIGHTLIFE
FOR THE DAILY NEWS.

22:03.282 --> 22:06.205
YOUR ANTICS
INSPIRED THE POETRY OF PROSE.

22:06.205 --> 22:09.579
AND YOUR ANTICS
EARNED YOU A LIFE SENTENCE.

22:09.579 --> 22:12.792
WELL, AT LEAST YOU STILL HAVE
THE BITE OF A STIFF DRINK.

22:12.792 --> 22:16.586
NOW, SINCE I'M SURE
YOU'RE PRESENTING AS MY LAWYER

22:16.586 --> 22:18.588
SO THIS CONVERSATION
CAN'T BE RECORDED,

22:18.588 --> 22:23.222
MY BURNING QUESTION IS,
FOR WHOSE TEAM ARE YOU PLAYING?

22:23.222 --> 22:25.595
I'M HERE
TO HELP EMILY FOLLOW THROUGH

22:25.595 --> 22:28.177
ON THE PROMISE
AMANDA CLARKE MADE TO YOU.

22:28.177 --> 22:30.179
EMILY? WOW.

22:30.179 --> 22:32.682
SHE'S SUCH
A DEVOTED FRIEND.

22:32.682 --> 22:35.314
THIS IS A MOTION
TO SET ASIDE YOUR CONVICTION.

22:35.314 --> 22:37.066
YOU'LL BE OUT
IN A FEW MONTHS.

22:37.066 --> 22:39.278
MS. THORNE
HAS ALSO TRANSFERRED FUNDS

22:39.278 --> 22:41.651
INTO YOUR CANTEEN ACCOUNT
FOR SUNDRIES.

22:41.651 --> 22:43.653
SUNDRIES?

22:43.653 --> 22:45.074
[ CHUCKLES ]

22:45.074 --> 22:47.697
I'M LOOKING FOR A LOT MORE

22:47.697 --> 22:50.660
THAN SOME SALVE
TO BRIGHTEN MY COMPLEXION.

22:52.161 --> 22:55.955
IT'S THE ONLY OPTION.

22:55.955 --> 22:57.587
IS IT?

22:57.587 --> 22:59.759
TELL MS. THORNE...

22:59.759 --> 23:02.802
I'M GOING WITH
WHAT'S BEHIND DOOR "G."

23:22.782 --> 23:25.735
Young Aiden: NO!

23:25.735 --> 23:29.789
NO, FATHER!

23:29.789 --> 23:33.162
[ Crying ] NO. NO, FATHER.

23:33.162 --> 23:35.875
AIDEN?

23:43.092 --> 23:44.674
[ CLICK ]

23:46.676 --> 23:48.718
[ SIGHS ]

23:48.718 --> 23:52.141
YOU KNOW, I...

23:52.141 --> 23:55.354
I HAVEN'T
BEEN BACK IN HERE...

23:55.354 --> 23:57.356
SINCE...
 [ RATTLING ]

23:57.356 --> 23:58.818
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

23:58.818 --> 24:02.021
YOU KNOW, EVERY TIME I'D,
UH, LOOK OUT MY BEDROOM WINDOW

24:02.021 --> 24:03.653
AND SEE
OUR CODE ON THE DOOR,

24:03.653 --> 24:05.695
I'D JUST HATE HIM
A LITTLE BIT MORE.

24:05.695 --> 24:07.827
"BOYS ONLY."

24:07.827 --> 24:09.368
YEAH, WE'D DEVISED THIS --
THIS CODE

24:09.368 --> 24:12.952
WHERE YOU'D JUST WRITE THE
BOTTOM HALVES OF LETTERS AND...

24:12.952 --> 24:14.664
SILLY, REALLY.
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:14.664 --> 24:16.706
HE MADE ME FEEL LIKE
WE WERE

24:16.706 --> 24:19.919
SHARING SOME --
SOME GREAT SECRET...

24:19.919 --> 24:22.131
WHEN, IN FACT,

24:22.131 --> 24:24.674
HE WAS THE ONE
KEEPING SECRETS FROM US.

24:24.674 --> 24:27.136
WELL,
YOU'RE KEEPING SOME, TOO.

24:27.136 --> 24:30.800
AIDEN, YOU HAVE TO TELL YOUR MOM
THAT COLLEEN IS DEAD.

24:30.800 --> 24:32.181
I CAN'T.

24:32.181 --> 24:34.764
I COULDN'T BRING MYSELF
TO TELL HER

24:34.764 --> 24:36.806
WHEN I THOUGHT THAT
SHE'D BEEN KIDNAPPED.

24:36.806 --> 24:38.768
MY MOTHER'S HOPE FOR HER
CHILDREN IS ALL SHE HAS LEFT.

24:38.768 --> 24:40.810
I CAN'T
TAKE THAT AWAY FROM HER.

24:40.810 --> 24:42.101
BUT YOU COULD
OFFER HER SOMETHING DIFFERENT --

24:42.101 --> 24:45.735
SOME ANSWERS
ABOUT THE MAN THAT SHE LOVED.

24:45.735 --> 24:47.106
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

24:47.106 --> 24:49.949
[ SIGHS ]

24:49.949 --> 24:51.911
YOU'RE NOT GONNA LEAVE THIS,
ARE YOU?

24:51.911 --> 24:54.534
HAVE I EVER?
 NO.

25:01.000 --> 25:02.001
WHAT IS IT?

25:03.583 --> 25:05.254
I'VE NEVER
SEEN THIS BEFORE,

25:05.254 --> 25:06.586
AND I'D KNOW
BECAUSE THIS TABLE

25:06.586 --> 25:10.129
IS THE LAST THING
MY FATHER AND I WORKED ON.

25:14.183 --> 25:16.596
"OSCAR CHAPMAN."

25:16.596 --> 25:18.598
WHO IS THAT?

25:18.598 --> 25:22.231
I DON'T KNOW.

25:22.231 --> 25:25.695
BUT MY FATHER
OBVIOUSLY WANTED ME TO.

25:25.695 --> 25:27.526
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

25:29.699 --> 25:32.491
WHATEVER YOU'RE HOLDING
OVER MASON TREADWELL, LET IT GO.

25:32.491 --> 25:34.493
WE NEED HIM OUT OF JAIL.

25:34.493 --> 25:38.077
OH, THE MAN CONFESSED...
TO MURDER

25:38.077 --> 25:40.710
AND SABOTAGING
THE GOVERNMENT PLANE YOU BOARDED

25:40.710 --> 25:42.752
IN THE DESPERATE ATTEMPT
TO TURN STATE'S EVIDENCE,

25:42.752 --> 25:45.374
AND, LEST WE FORGET
HIS MOST HEINOUS SIN,

25:45.374 --> 25:49.048
TRYING TO
FRAME ME FOR IT ALL...

25:49.048 --> 25:52.011
ON MY WEDDING DAY.

25:52.011 --> 25:53.633
WHICH IS WHY
YOU HAD HIM PUT AWAY.

25:53.633 --> 25:55.014
[ LAUGHS ]

25:55.014 --> 25:57.096
I ASSURE YOU,
I DID NOTHING OF THE SORT.

25:57.096 --> 25:59.518
[ GLASS THUDS ]
 OR IS THIS LUNACY

25:59.518 --> 26:01.440
A RUSE TO ENTER MY SUITE?

26:01.440 --> 26:05.895
OH, WHAT'S THE MATTER?
FRENCH GRASS NOT GREENER?

26:05.895 --> 26:09.108
WERE WE NOT BOUND BY OUR SINS,
I WOULD BE NOWHERE NEAR YOU.

26:09.108 --> 26:11.901
[ SCOFFS ]
 EMILY'S INTERESTED
IN FLIGHT 197.

26:11.901 --> 26:13.322
AND I THINK
MASON KNOWS WHY.

26:13.322 --> 26:15.695
OH, HE KNOWS NOTHING
BUT HOW TO SPIN A TALE.

26:15.695 --> 26:18.327
AND AS LONG AS EMILY
IS YOUR ENEMY,

26:18.327 --> 26:20.660
WELL,
SHE'S AN ALLY TO ME.

26:20.660 --> 26:22.331
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

26:22.331 --> 26:23.703
[ BEEP ]

26:23.703 --> 26:25.544
HELLO?

26:25.544 --> 26:26.916
YES.

26:28.838 --> 26:32.261
ARE YOU SURE?

26:32.261 --> 26:34.473
THANK YOU.

26:34.473 --> 26:35.594
[ BEEP ]

26:35.594 --> 26:38.387
GUESS WHO VISITED MASON
IN JAIL TODAY.

26:38.387 --> 26:39.769
STEVIE. HMM.

26:39.769 --> 26:42.181
IT SEEMS LIKE YOUR EX-WIFE
IS UP TO HER OLD TRICKS.

26:42.181 --> 26:45.564
AND IF SHE'S WORKING FOR EMILY,
GOD HELP HER.

26:47.687 --> 26:49.358
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

26:57.286 --> 26:59.659
IT WAS GOOD
TO MEET YOU.

26:59.659 --> 27:01.370
I WISH YOU
ONLY HAPPINESS.

27:01.370 --> 27:03.162
THANK YOU,
MRS. MATHIS.

27:03.162 --> 27:05.164
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
I'LL BE OUTSIDE.

27:05.164 --> 27:07.747
YEAH.

27:07.747 --> 27:10.169
SHE'S A LOVELY GIRL.

27:10.169 --> 27:13.172
[ DOOR OPENS ]
 [ Sighing ] YEAH.

27:13.172 --> 27:16.175
YEAH, SHE IS.

27:16.175 --> 27:18.597
MUM, PLEASE SIT DOWN.

27:18.597 --> 27:20.760
I NEED TO TALK TO YOU.

27:20.760 --> 27:22.972
UM...

27:22.972 --> 27:26.766
LOOK, I-I HAVEN'T
BEEN HONEST WITH YOU.

27:26.766 --> 27:29.358
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]
EMILY AND I --

27:29.358 --> 27:31.771
WE AREN'T TOGETHER.

27:31.771 --> 27:34.033
I NEEDED SOMEONE
TO COME WITH ME,

27:34.033 --> 27:36.445
AND SHE WAS THE ONLY PERSON
THAT I WOULD HAVE BY MY SIDE.

27:36.445 --> 27:38.077
WHY LIE TO ME?

27:38.077 --> 27:40.700
I JUST...

27:40.700 --> 27:44.083
WANTED TO GIVE YOU SOME
HAPPY NEWS AFTER MY ABSENCE.

27:44.083 --> 27:46.545
I'M SORRY.

27:46.545 --> 27:49.749
I UNDERSTOOD
WHEN YOU LEFT HOME AT 16.

27:49.749 --> 27:51.590
LIFE HERE WAS HORRIBLE.

27:51.590 --> 27:55.674
AND YOU KEPT IN TOUCH
AS WELL AS YOUNG MEN DO.

27:55.674 --> 27:56.926
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

27:56.926 --> 27:58.677
BUT WHEN YOU DISAPPEARED
JUST LIKE YOUR SISTER,

27:58.677 --> 28:00.800
I WONDERED
WHAT I'D DONE WRONG.

28:05.304 --> 28:10.479
COLLEEN DIDN'T RUN AWAY,
MUM.

28:10.479 --> 28:12.441
SOME MEN TOOK HER.

28:12.441 --> 28:15.735
AND THEY PROMISED
THAT THEY'D BRING HER BACK

28:15.735 --> 28:18.277
IF DAD PLANTED A BOMB
ON THE PLANE.

28:18.277 --> 28:21.280
8 YEARS AGO,

28:21.280 --> 28:23.823
I TRACKED DOWN
THE MEN WHO HAD TAKEN HER,

28:23.823 --> 28:25.624
AND I FOUND HER.

28:30.920 --> 28:33.132
I'M SORRY, MUM.

28:33.132 --> 28:36.215
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]
SHE'S GONE.

28:38.717 --> 28:42.301
[ GASPS ]
AND WHAT ABOUT THE MEN?

28:42.301 --> 28:45.684
ALSO DEAD.

28:45.684 --> 28:48.898
GOOD.

28:48.898 --> 28:51.020
[ GASPS ]
I NEVER LET MYSELF BELIEVE

28:51.020 --> 28:52.691
YOUR FATHER
WAS A MONSTER.

29:00.699 --> 29:02.071
I'M SORRY, MUM.

29:04.533 --> 29:07.126
[ SNIFFLES ]

29:07.126 --> 29:10.129
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

29:12.962 --> 29:14.753
YOU SNUCK OUT.

29:23.262 --> 29:24.884
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT ABOUT NOLAN?

29:24.884 --> 29:26.886
AREN'T YOU WORRIED ABOUT
JEOPARDIZING YOUR PARTNERSHIP?

29:26.886 --> 29:28.848
I THINK YOU MEAN
INTERNSHIP.

29:28.848 --> 29:31.440
HE TRIED TO GET ME TO
SIGN A TOTALLY BOGUS CONTRACT.

29:31.440 --> 29:32.771
AND WHY
WOULD HE DO THAT?

29:32.771 --> 29:34.773
'CAUSE HE KNOWS MYCLONE
IS NEXT-GEN TWITTER LEVEL,

29:34.773 --> 29:36.775
AND HE WANTS TO
GET HIS NAME TRENDING.

29:36.775 --> 29:38.737
I THOUGHT WE WERE TIGHT,
BUT IT SEEMS

29:38.737 --> 29:40.739
THE ONLY PERSON THAT GUY JUMPS
FOR AT A MINUTE'S NOTICE

29:40.739 --> 29:42.571
IS THAT BLOND GIRL --
EMILY.

29:42.571 --> 29:45.164
AND I KNOW
THEY'VE NEVER EVEN --
 EVER.

29:45.164 --> 29:47.366
THOUGH SHE HAS MANY MEN
AT HER BECK AND CALL,

29:47.366 --> 29:48.908
INCLUDING MY FRIEND JACK.

29:48.908 --> 29:51.750
PORTER, RIGHT?
 YEAH.

29:51.750 --> 29:53.752
YEAH, NOLAN HAD ME HELP
HIM THE DAY I GOT HERE --

29:53.752 --> 29:56.916
SOME FILE-DECODING EMERGENCY
AT A LAW FIRM.

29:56.916 --> 29:59.128
JACK.
 YEAH.

29:59.128 --> 30:00.549
SO, THEY HAVE
THEIR LITTLE GANG

30:00.549 --> 30:02.341
THAT I GUESS
I'M NOT A PART OF.

30:04.844 --> 30:07.636
TELL ME ABOUT IT.

30:07.636 --> 30:10.850
ACTUALLY, I KNOW SOMEONE
WHO CAN HELP YOU.

30:10.850 --> 30:12.852
WHO?

30:12.852 --> 30:14.693
MY BROTHER.

30:26.445 --> 30:29.248
I HAD YOU
WHEN I WAS 19.

30:29.248 --> 30:30.499
I DIDN'T KNOW
HOW TO BE A FATHER.

30:30.499 --> 30:33.873
INSTEAD OF RAISING YOU,
I RAISED AN EMPIRE.

30:33.873 --> 30:35.624
AND OUR RELATIONSHIP
SUFFERED.

30:35.624 --> 30:37.796
AND IT WAS EASIER TO HAVE
A CONNECTION WITH YOUR SONS.

30:37.796 --> 30:38.918
NO.

30:38.918 --> 30:41.130
IT'S JUST,
BY MY SECOND MARRIAGE,

30:41.130 --> 30:42.761
I WAS A BETTER FATHER.

30:42.761 --> 30:44.763
[ SIGHS ]

30:44.763 --> 30:47.806
MARGAUX.

30:50.469 --> 30:53.852
MY AWKWARDNESS
WITH YOU --

30:53.852 --> 30:56.815
IT'S BECAUSE
OF MY REGRET.

31:05.074 --> 31:07.076
WHAT IS THIS?

31:07.076 --> 31:09.488
MY 5-YEAR PLAN
FOR THE COMPANY.

31:09.488 --> 31:13.082
WE SHOULD BE FURTHER ALONG
WITH NEW MEDIA ACQUISITIONS.

31:13.082 --> 31:14.663
YOU'RE BEING TOO LAX.

31:14.663 --> 31:17.126
AND YOUR POSITION
ON THE DST DEAL LAST YEAR --

31:17.126 --> 31:20.129
THAT WAS A MISTAKE.
 A MISTAKE.

31:21.710 --> 31:24.883
I WOULD HAVE
HANDLED IT DIFFERENTLY, PAPA.

31:24.883 --> 31:28.507
[ PAPERS RUSTLE ]

31:28.507 --> 31:30.429
THEN TELL ME.

31:37.856 --> 31:41.860
OSCAR CHAPMAN WAS A FREELANCE
REPORTER BASED IN LONDON.

31:41.860 --> 31:44.233
WORKED FOR LeMARCHAL MEDIA
IN '93.

31:44.233 --> 31:46.525
DIED IN A CAR ACCIDENT.

31:46.525 --> 31:48.407
IT'S ANOTHER DEAD END.

31:48.407 --> 31:49.618
DON'T LOSE HOPE YET.
 WELL, WHY NOT?

31:49.618 --> 31:50.990
THIS WHOLE THING'S
BEEN A WASTE OF TIME.

31:50.990 --> 31:52.621
YOU KNOW
THAT'S NOT TRUE.

31:52.621 --> 31:54.623
YOU RECONNECTED
WITH YOUR MOTHER.

31:54.623 --> 31:56.915
YEAH.
YEAH, YOU'RE RIGHT.

31:59.338 --> 32:01.670
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU'VE BEEN
CARRYING ALL OF THAT.

32:01.670 --> 32:04.713
EMILY...THANK YOU.

32:04.713 --> 32:08.717
I KNOW YOU HAVE A CRISIS HERE
WITH VICTORIA CLOSING IN,

32:08.717 --> 32:10.719
BUT...

32:10.719 --> 32:13.512
YOU STAYED BY ME, SO...

32:13.512 --> 32:16.555
WE'VE ALWAYS BEEN THERE
FOR EACH OTHER.

32:23.692 --> 32:26.525
[ BREATHES HEAVILY ]

32:26.525 --> 32:28.827
I'VE MISSED YOU, TOO.

32:31.280 --> 32:33.662
[ SNIFFLES ]

32:35.414 --> 32:38.417
[ BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY ]

32:45.084 --> 32:47.296
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]
 [ KEYS JANGLING ]

32:49.298 --> 32:51.890
Guard: OPEN UP.

32:51.890 --> 32:53.972
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

32:59.268 --> 33:01.060
[ SNIFFING ]

33:11.200 --> 33:14.073
[ COUGHING ]

33:15.824 --> 33:18.207
[ GAGGING ]

33:20.209 --> 33:22.211
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

33:24.623 --> 33:28.677
[ ALARM BLARING ]
 OPEN UNIT 28! NOW!

33:37.306 --> 33:39.558
WHAT THE HELL
KIND OF GAME ARE YOU PLAYING?

33:39.558 --> 33:42.641
I ASSUME THIS VISIT ISN'T
AN OVERDUE "THANK YOU"

33:42.641 --> 33:44.853
FOR SIGNING OVER
THE DEED TO GRAYSON MANOR.

33:44.853 --> 33:47.446
YOU NEVER GAVE A DAMN
ABOUT THAT HOUSE.

33:47.446 --> 33:50.239
YOU'VE BEEN AFTER MY FAMILY
FROM THE START.

33:50.239 --> 33:53.452
WHAT'S YOUR INTEREST
IN MASON TREADWELL?

33:55.614 --> 33:58.207
MY CLIENTS
ARE NONE OF YOUR CONCERN.

33:58.207 --> 34:00.619
OH, I THOUGHT
YOU'D CLAM UP...

34:00.619 --> 34:02.961
SO I BROUGHT ALONG
AN OLD FRIEND.

34:02.961 --> 34:05.964
[ SCOFFS ]

34:05.964 --> 34:07.546
[ SNIFFS ]

34:07.546 --> 34:09.088
THERE WAS A TIME
WHEN THE SMELL ALONE

34:09.088 --> 34:12.511
WAS ENOUGH TO MAKE YOU SLOPPY
AND SO, SO CHATTY.

34:12.511 --> 34:14.513
GET THE HELL OUT OF MY ROOM.
 I PROBABLY SHOULD...

34:14.513 --> 34:16.725
[ BOTTLE THUDS ]

34:16.725 --> 34:19.138
...SINCE ANYONE YOU TRY TO
TAKE INTO YOUR CONFIDENCE

34:19.138 --> 34:20.889
ENDS UP DECEASED.

34:22.731 --> 34:24.943
OR DIDN'T YOU KNOW
THAT MASON TREADWELL

34:24.943 --> 34:26.525
WAS FOUND DEAD IN HIS CELL
TONIGHT?

34:26.525 --> 34:28.947
WHAT?
 YOU MEDDLED
WHERE YOU SHOULDN'T,

34:28.947 --> 34:31.739
WITH NO CONCERN
FOR THE CONSEQUENCE.

34:31.739 --> 34:35.154
YOU MAY BE SOBER, BUT YOU STILL
CAN'T THINK CLEARLY.

34:37.246 --> 34:39.408
WATCH YOUR BACK,
STEVIE...

34:39.408 --> 34:42.831
AND THOSE
OF THE PEOPLE YOU LOVE.

34:52.210 --> 34:55.804
[ SPEAKING FRENCH ]

34:55.804 --> 34:57.426
[ BEEP ]

34:57.426 --> 35:00.849
IF MY, UH,
HIGH-SCHOOL FRENCH SERVES,

35:00.849 --> 35:02.141
ALLOW ME TO ANSWER.

35:02.141 --> 35:03.682
YOUR SON WAS BUSY

35:03.682 --> 35:05.934
BLATANTLY TRADING YOUR NAME
FOR FAVORS

35:05.934 --> 35:08.106
AND ACTING
LIKE HIS ASCENSION

35:08.106 --> 35:10.108
WAS A FAIT ACCOMPLI.
 [ CHUCKLES ]

35:10.108 --> 35:12.110
HE WASN'T TO SHARE THAT.

35:12.110 --> 35:14.112
MM. DOMMAGE.

35:14.112 --> 35:16.735
WELL, SINCE HE'S ALREADY
BOTCHED THAT TASK,

35:16.735 --> 35:19.948
ALLOW ME TO CONGRATULATE YOU
ON YOUR RETIREMENT...

35:19.948 --> 35:24.002
THOUGH ANNOUNCING IT SO EARLY
IS QUITE THE GAMBLE.

35:24.002 --> 35:26.004
I MEAN, IMAGINE THE PANIC

35:26.004 --> 35:27.796
THAT'LL RIPPLE
THROUGH YOUR COMPANY,

35:27.796 --> 35:30.959
MAKING IT EASY FOR VULTURES
TO SWOOP IN AND FEAST.

35:30.959 --> 35:32.341
AND YOU ARE ONE OF THEM.

35:32.341 --> 35:33.592
AH, FOUL OF ME,
PERHAPS,

35:33.592 --> 35:36.555
BUT YOUR LOYA DEAL
WAS MY FIRST CARCASS.

35:36.555 --> 35:38.757
THE ACQUISITION
WILL BE ANNOUNCED

35:38.757 --> 35:40.929
IN THE "JOURNAL"
TOMORROW.

35:50.569 --> 35:53.192
[ WAVES CRASHING ]

35:53.192 --> 35:55.984
Margaux: DANIEL.

35:55.984 --> 35:57.986
MY FATHER IS GROOMING ME

35:57.986 --> 36:00.779
TO TAKE OVER
THE LeMARCHAL EMPIRE.

36:00.779 --> 36:02.831
REALLY?
 MM-HMM.

36:02.831 --> 36:07.456
SO I WANTED TO POP BY
[CHUCKLES] AND THANK YOU.

36:07.456 --> 36:09.047
I DIDN'T DO ANYTHING.

36:09.047 --> 36:10.919
YOU'VE BEEN
A GOOD FRIEND...

36:10.919 --> 36:13.091
BESIDE ME
FOR THE WHOLE RIDE,

36:13.091 --> 36:15.924
SINCE I WAS
A 16-YEAR-OLD GIRL

36:15.924 --> 36:18.297
COMPLAINING
ABOUT HER FATHER,

36:18.297 --> 36:21.139
UNTIL RIGHT NOW, TONIGHT.

36:21.139 --> 36:23.141
YEAH.
 [ CHUCKLES ]

36:23.141 --> 36:25.143
YOU KNOW,
YOU WERE ALWAYS SPECIAL.

36:25.143 --> 36:26.435
THAT'S WHY
I CHALLENGED YOU

36:26.435 --> 36:28.517
TO EVERY IMPOSSIBLE SKI SLOPE
WHEN WE WERE KIDS.

36:28.517 --> 36:32.150
YOU JUST --
YOU JUST KEPT WINNING.

36:42.080 --> 36:43.662
YEAH.

36:43.662 --> 36:46.034
WE'LL MAKE A GREAT TEAM,
DANIEL.

36:46.034 --> 36:48.166
AND IF I'M GOING TO
RUN THE COMPANY,

36:48.166 --> 36:52.130
I'LL NEED GREATNESS
BY MY SIDE.

36:52.130 --> 36:54.132
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

36:54.132 --> 36:56.505
SO...
 COME ON.
LET'S CELEBRATE, THEN.

36:56.505 --> 36:57.716
WHOA, WHOA, WHOA,
WHOA, WHOA.
 [ CORK POPS ]

36:57.716 --> 36:58.717
AH!
 [ GIGGLES ]

37:01.099 --> 37:04.052
[ LOCK BEEPS ]

37:04.052 --> 37:07.476
HEY. YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
ANSWERING YOUR CALL--

37:07.476 --> 37:09.478
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

37:09.478 --> 37:12.060
[ SNIFFS ]

37:12.060 --> 37:14.653
WHAT'S GOING ON?

37:14.653 --> 37:17.065
I...
[ SNIFFLES ]

37:17.065 --> 37:20.449
I HEARD MASON DIED,
AND I'M -- I'M --

37:20.449 --> 37:23.071
[ Voice breaking ]
I'M IN OVER MY HEAD HERE.

37:23.071 --> 37:25.163
THIS DAMN PLACE, JACK.
I'M SORRY.

37:25.163 --> 37:26.535
DON'T APOLOGIZE.

37:26.535 --> 37:30.459
YOU HAVE NOTHING TO DO
WITH WHAT HAPPENED TO MASON.

37:30.459 --> 37:32.871
I THOUGHT I WAS HELPING,
AND I --

37:32.871 --> 37:35.083
AND I ENDED UP
HURTING SOMEONE.

37:35.083 --> 37:36.675
GOD, I NEVER WANTED YOU
TO SEE ME LIKE THIS.

37:36.675 --> 37:38.467
I WANT YOU TO --
I WANT YOU TO GO.

37:38.467 --> 37:40.679
JUST GO, PLEASE.

37:40.679 --> 37:44.683
[ CRIES ]

37:44.683 --> 37:46.345
I'M GETTING YOU
OUT OF HERE.

37:46.345 --> 37:49.348
[ SNIFFLES, GASPS ]

37:51.350 --> 37:53.101
NO. OH, NO.

37:53.101 --> 37:56.104
NO, I DON'T --

37:56.104 --> 37:57.946
[ ZIPPER OPENS ]
 JACK. [ SNIFFLES ]

37:57.946 --> 38:00.819
I DON'T WANT TO BE THE FIRST
BAD MEMORY IN YOUR NEW HOUSE.

38:00.819 --> 38:02.200
[ Chuckling ]
YOU WON'T BE.

38:02.200 --> 38:04.533
I'M TAKING YOU HOME
TO L.A., OKAY?

38:06.955 --> 38:09.868
COME WITH ME.

38:09.868 --> 38:12.120
PLEASE COME WITH ME,
AND WE COULD START OVER.

38:12.120 --> 38:14.373
AND YOU COULD
BRING EMILY

38:14.373 --> 38:15.754
'CAUSE
SHE HAS TO STOP THIS.

38:15.754 --> 38:18.337
SHE CAN'T.

38:18.337 --> 38:21.550
THIS IS EVERYTHING
TO HER.

38:21.550 --> 38:24.553
[ INHALES DEEPLY,
SIGHS ]

38:24.553 --> 38:26.134
AND I'M --

38:26.134 --> 38:28.687
I'M COMING BACK HERE
TO HELP HER FINISH.

38:28.687 --> 38:31.890
WELL...
[ SNIFFLES ]

38:31.890 --> 38:35.434
...MAYBE DANIEL'S RIGHT.

38:35.434 --> 38:37.736
YOU LOVE EMILY,
DON'T YOU?

38:47.706 --> 38:50.118
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

38:50.118 --> 38:52.120
I MISS YOU.
 MM.

38:52.120 --> 38:54.713
IT'S BEEN
AN EVENTFUL FEW DAYS.

38:54.713 --> 38:56.505
YEAH, I AGREE.

38:56.505 --> 38:58.917
CONRAD HAS
DECIDED TO DECLARE WAR.

38:58.917 --> 39:00.298
WELL, THEN, SO HAVE I.

39:00.298 --> 39:02.511
I RAN STEVIE GRAYSON
OUT OF TOWN,

39:02.511 --> 39:05.464
AND NOW IT'S TIME TO TEST
MY THEORY ABOUT EMILY THORNE.

39:05.464 --> 39:09.057
SEEMS WE'RE BOTH AT WAR.

39:09.057 --> 39:10.679
HMM.

39:12.931 --> 39:15.524
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

39:15.524 --> 39:17.185
WE HAVE RESERVATIONS.

39:17.185 --> 39:19.317
WE'RE NOT
GOING TO DINNER.

39:38.086 --> 39:41.259
[ GASPING ]

39:41.259 --> 39:43.051
[ GRUNTING ]

39:43.051 --> 39:44.673
WHAT? NO.

39:44.673 --> 39:47.055
OH, MY GOD. OH, MY GOD.

39:47.055 --> 39:48.346
GET ME OUT OF HERE!

39:48.346 --> 39:50.138
HELP! HELP!

39:50.138 --> 39:51.770
[ SCREAMING ]

39:53.852 --> 39:55.434
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

39:55.434 --> 39:58.396
NOLAN ROSS?

39:58.396 --> 40:00.649
AND YOU SAID
YOU DIDN'T NEED SUNDRIES.

40:00.649 --> 40:04.022
GOD, YOUR SKIN.
YOU JUST LOOK SO ALIVE.

40:04.022 --> 40:06.445
ALL CREDIT DUE TO
EMILY'S FACE CREAM,

40:06.445 --> 40:08.447
WHICH CONTAINED
A JAPANESE HERB

40:08.447 --> 40:12.080
THAT [CHUCKLES] MAKES THE BODY
MIMIC DEATH FOR 12 HOURS.

40:12.080 --> 40:15.494
WHAT THE HELL?

40:15.494 --> 40:17.335
WE'RE OUTSIDE
OF THE GATES?

40:17.335 --> 40:20.088
WELL, THAT WAS YOUR REQUEST,
RIGHT?

40:20.088 --> 40:22.671
CASH AND A NEW IDENTITY.

40:22.671 --> 40:26.044
MY PRIVATE JET WILL
WHISK YOU AWAY TO THE MALDIVES,

40:26.044 --> 40:27.676
WHERE EMILY
HAS PROVIDED YOU

40:27.676 --> 40:29.718
WITH THE PERFECT
WRITER'S RETREAT --

40:29.718 --> 40:32.721
A BUNGALOW OFF THE GRID.

40:32.721 --> 40:35.934
WHICH MAKES ME

40:35.934 --> 40:38.056
A PART OF ONE OF
MS. THORNE'S INFAMOUS PLANS

40:38.056 --> 40:39.938
IN A STORY
THAT SHE'S OBVIOUSLY

40:39.938 --> 40:42.230
STILL VERY COMMITTED
TO FINISHING.

40:42.230 --> 40:44.192
WE NEED TO KNOW THAT
WE HAVE YOUR ALLEGIANCE.

40:44.192 --> 40:46.615
I ONLY
BARTERED WITH VICTORIA

40:46.615 --> 40:49.618
BECAUSE, FRANKLY,
I'D LOST FAITH.

40:49.618 --> 40:52.531
BUT CONSIDER ME REBORN...

40:52.531 --> 40:54.533
DEAD THOUGH I MAY BE.

40:54.533 --> 40:56.164
[ CHUCKLES ]

40:56.164 --> 40:59.127
YOU KNOW, I NEVER THOUGHT
I WOULD SAY THIS, BUT...

40:59.127 --> 41:02.000
IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU,
MASON.

41:02.000 --> 41:03.381
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:03.381 --> 41:05.213
AND WHAT
SHALL WE TALK ABOUT

41:05.213 --> 41:08.426
IN OUR SOON-TO-BE-RESUMED RIDE
TO THE AIRFIELD?

41:08.426 --> 41:11.219
OH, WELL,
I'VE GOT A FEW QUESTIONS

41:11.219 --> 41:14.052
ABOUT ANOTHER
DEAD REPORTER.

41:14.052 --> 41:17.225
YOU EVER HEARD OF,
UH, OSCAR CHAPMAN?

41:23.772 --> 41:24.983
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:24.983 --> 41:27.235
[ SMOOCHES ]
 [ SIGHS ]

41:38.206 --> 41:40.208
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

41:43.211 --> 41:45.043
[ BEEP ]

41:45.043 --> 41:47.045
HEY, NOLAN.

41:49.127 --> 41:52.130
WHAT?

41:52.130 --> 41:55.183
YEAH, I'LL TELL HIM.

41:55.183 --> 41:57.185
OKAY, BYE.
 [ BEEP ]

41:57.185 --> 41:59.638
WHAT? HAS MASON
BEEN NEUTRALIZED?

41:59.638 --> 42:02.060
HE'S IN THE AIR.

42:02.060 --> 42:05.023
BUT BEFORE HE LEFT,

42:05.023 --> 42:08.406
HE TOLD NOLAN THAT OSCAR CHAPMAN
FAKED HIS OWN DEATH.

42:08.406 --> 42:10.699
YOU DON'T THINK HE JUST
WANTS US CHASING OUR TAILS?

42:10.699 --> 42:14.032
WHAT, AND FURTHER DELAY
HIS MAGNUM OPUS? NO WAY.

42:14.032 --> 42:17.035
THE MAN WHO MIGHT KNOW
PASCAL'S CONNECTION

42:17.035 --> 42:19.457
COULD STILL BE ALIVE.

42:19.457 --> 42:23.041
THEN WE BETTER PRAY
WE CAN FIND HIM.
